President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Joseph Dawson of South Carolina as a Judge on the United States District Court for the District of South Carolina. Currently serving as the County Attorney for Charleston County, South Carolina, Dawson is responsible for managing and overseeing all legal matters for the county and its officials. He also operates his own solo law practice, specializing in general civil litigation and offering strategic advice to small businesses. Dawson holds a B.A. from The Citadel, The Military College of South Carolina, and a J.D. from the University of South Carolina School of Law.